## 1. Purpose & Context

This PRD defines the front-end architecture, component behavior, interaction logic, and UX philosophy for the Sprint Planning feature within the Architect OS Pro Suite. It is intended to serve as the authoritative reference for Antigravity during all incremental build prompts for this feature.

### What This Feature Is

Sprint Planning is the execution translation layer of Architect OS. It is where a founder moves from strategic clarity — knowing their stage, their gaps, their 12-month vision — into a structured, actionable 12-week execution plan. By the time a founder completes this section, they should have a first-draft sprint plan: capability areas classified, initiatives defined, milestones outlined, and success criteria established.

### What This Feature Is Not

Sprint Planning is not a task management system, a project management tool, or an operational tracker. It operates at the strategic initiative and milestone level — not at the task or subtask level. The execution section (separate) is where plans are launched and tracked. Sprint Planning is where the plan is created.

### Design Philosophy

The platform operates as an observational, coaching-oriented tool — not a prescriptive system that tells founders what to do. Every interaction should feel like working with a sophisticated peer advisor, not filling out a form. The AI elements support and suggest; they never auto-generate without founder initiation. Friction is minimized at entry and concentrated at the right moments: when it creates clarity, not when it creates busywork.

