## 2. The 3P Framework — Core Planning Logic

All sprint planning logic is organized around the 3P Framework. Every developer building this feature must understand this framework as it governs the entire information architecture, classification logic, and UX behavior of the sprint board.

### PRIORITIZE

The three capability areas receiving full strategic attention this quarter. These are major lifts requiring real resources, dedicated owner assignment, and multiple coordinated initiatives. This is where the quarter's momentum is built.

**Initiative guidance:**
- Recommended: 2–3 initiatives per capability area
- Maximum: 3 initiatives per capability area
- Each initiative should represent a meaningful strategic workstream
- Requires at least 2 milestones per initiative before sprint lock

### PLANT

Three capability areas being seeded for future quarters. These are intentionally small lifts — tracking a new metric, having a key conversation, building a data foundation. Plant work enables future Prioritize work. It should feel lightweight to define.

**Initiative guidance:**
- Recommended: 1 initiative per capability area
- Maximum: 2 initiatives per capability area
- If it needs more than 2 initiatives, it may belong in Prioritize

### PROGRESSIVELY ITERATE

Three capability areas in ongoing refinement mode. Work has already been done in these areas; they require continued attention as the agency evolves. Examples: refining ICP as the agency matures, tweaking pricing structures, optimizing a delivery process already in place.

**Initiative guidance:**
- Maximum: 1 initiative per capability area
- If more than 1 initiative is needed, the area may actually be a Prioritize
- These get attention when capacity allows — not at the expense of Prioritize work

> **Important:** Any of the 25 capability areas can fall into any 3P bucket depending on the agency's stage and quarter. The 3P classification is contextual, not fixed. The three buckets are not equal in weight — Prioritize carries the primary strategic load of the quarter.

### Total Initiative Cap Reference

| Tier | Cap | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Prioritize | Up to 9 total (3 capability areas × 3 max each) | Soft guidance targets 6–7 in practice |
| Plant | Up to 6 total (3 capability areas × 2 max each) | Platform nudges toward 1 per area |
| Progressively Iterate | Up to 3 total (3 capability areas × 1 max each) | Hard cap — 1 per area, no exceptions |
| Total Ceiling | 18 initiatives maximum | Platform coaching anchors toward 10–13 as realistic target |

