## 3. Overall Founder Workflow

The following describes the complete intended journey a founder takes through Sprint Planning. Antigravity should use this as the behavioral reference for how all components connect and sequence. This is not a UI sitemap — it is the lived experience the platform must enable.

### Phase 1 — Pre-Sprint Context (Already Completed Upstream)

Before reaching Sprint Planning, the founder has already completed:

- AE Ladder Assessment — stage placement confirmed
- Maturity & Readiness Audit — 125-checkpoint diagnostic with capability scores
- Horizon Declaration — 36/24/12-month vision defined (qualitative + quantitative)
- Roadmap Review — 12-month vision broken into 4 directional sprints
- Sprint Goal Definition — the specific outcome statement for this 12-week block
- Quarter Map — 3P capability selection completed (9 of 25 capability areas classified)

> By the time a founder reaches the Sprint Board, they have a sprint goal and 9 classified capability areas. Sprint Planning translates that structure into executable initiatives and milestones.

### Phase 2 — Initiative Creation (Sprint Board)

The founder lands on the Sprint Board in Capability View. They see three columns (Prioritize, Plant, Progressively Iterate) with their 9 classified capability cards distributed across them. From here they:

- Click into any capability area to open the Capability Card Modal
- Review capability context: description, stage-calibrated "what good looks like," maturity score
- Add initiatives via inline quick-add (name only) or the full initiative entry form
- Work across capability areas in any order — no forced sequence
- Toggle to Initiative View to see all initiatives across 3P columns simultaneously
- Use the Strategic Advisor panel at any point for coaching support

### Phase 3 — Milestone Definition

Once the initiative set feels complete enough, the founder adds milestones to each initiative. This can happen immediately after creating an initiative or in a separate session. They:

- Click into any initiative to open the Initiative Card Modal
- Add milestones via inline quick-add or by clicking into the milestone for full detail
- Define outcome, measure, owner, timeline, and dependencies per milestone
- Navigate between initiatives using breadcrumb without closing the modal

### Phase 4 — Sprint Lock

When the founder is ready to commit the plan:

- They click "Review & Lock Sprint" from the Sprint Board
- System surfaces a completion review: which initiatives are incomplete, which capability areas have no initiatives
- Founder resolves any gaps or consciously proceeds with incomplete items
- On confirmation, the system generates a Sprint Executive Summary via GPT synthesis
- The locked sprint creates a snapshot that feeds the Execution module
- The executive summary becomes a persistent element accessible from the top bar

