## 4. Navigation Architecture — The Unified Modal System

### Core Principle

All three levels of sprint planning content — Capability Areas, Initiatives, and Milestones — use the same popup modal window pattern. The layout, split structure, and interaction logic are identical across all three levels. The founder learns the interface once and applies it everywhere.

### Single Modal, Drills In Place

There are no stacking modals. When a founder drills from a capability card into an initiative, and from an initiative into a milestone, it is the same modal container transitioning its content. One active modal at a time, always.

### Breadcrumb Navigation

The upper-left corner of the modal always displays the full cascade of where the founder is:

```
Prioritize  >  Cash Flow Forecasting  >  Build Financial Dashboard  >  Audit Data Sources
```

- Each breadcrumb node is clickable and navigates back up to that level
- The breadcrumb always starts from the 3P classification (Prioritize / Plant / Iterate)
- It is persistent on first entry, fifth entry, and every entry — it never disappears
- If an initiative is reclassified (e.g., moved from Prioritize to Plant), the breadcrumb updates automatically because it reads from backend metadata
- A back arrow accompanies the breadcrumb for quick single-level navigation

### Modal Layout — Split Panel Structure

All three modal levels use the same split layout:

| Panel | Content |
|---|---|
| Left Panel | Primary content — the list of children at this level (initiatives inside capability, milestones inside initiative) plus inline quick-add at bottom |
| Right Panel | Contextual metadata — level-specific fields, status, comments/activity, change history |
| Bottom Corner | Strategic Advisor trigger — accessible from all modal levels |

### Inline Expand Pattern

Within each modal's content list, clicking an item expands it inline to show a compact editable summary. This is the quick-edit state. A pencil icon within the expanded row opens the full modal for that item. Two interaction depths always available: inline quick-edit for small changes, full modal for complete review.

