## 5. Capability Card Modal

Opened when a founder clicks any capability area card on the Sprint Board. This is the coaching and orientation layer — it provides context that helps founders write better initiatives.

### Left Panel Content

| Element | Description | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Capability Name | Large heading at top of panel | |
| Capability Description | What this capability area is designed to address and enable | 2–3 sentences |
| What Good Looks Like | Stage-calibrated statement of what "at stage" performance looks like for this founder's AE Ladder placement | Pulled from platform knowledge base, stage-specific |
| Initiative List | All initiatives associated with this capability area, shown as expandable rows | Inline quick-edit on click; pencil icon opens full initiative modal |
| Inline Quick-Add | Plus button or empty row at bottom of initiative list. Type a name, press enter to save. Creates an incomplete initiative immediately. | No form, no fields beyond name at this stage |
| Add Initiative Button | Above the quick-add row. Opens the full Initiative Entry Form modal. | Always visible, not competing with quick-add |

### Right Panel Content

| Element | Description | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Maturity Score | Current capability-level maturity score from the Maturity & Readiness Audit | Shown as percentage + visual progress indicator |
| Stage Tag | Below Stage / At Stage / Ahead of Stage relative to current AE Ladder placement | Color-coded tag |
| Checkpoint Context | Directional summary of which checkpoints within this capability are flagged — not individual scores, but thematic context about where the gaps live | |
| Comments & Activity | Founder-level notes and activity log for this capability area | Not initiative-level — this is capability-level commentary |
| 3P Classification Tag | Prioritize / Plant / Progressively Iterate badge showing which bucket this capability is in | Read from metadata; not editable here |

### Empty State (First Time, Zero Initiatives)

When a capability card is opened with no initiatives yet created:

- Full capability context is shown (description, what good looks like, maturity score)
- Initiative list area shows a single empty state message: "No initiatives yet — add one below"
- The inline quick-add row is present and ready for input
- The Add Initiative button is present above it
- No auto-generated suggestions appear — the Strategic Advisor panel is available in the bottom corner if the founder wants coaching support

