## 7. Initiative Card Modal

The full initiative workspace. Opened by clicking the pencil icon within an expanded initiative row, or by clicking "Add Initiative" from the Sprint Board's initiative view.

### Left Panel Content

| Element | Description | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Initiative Name | Editable heading at top | |
| Initiative Description | Editable field combining "What We Are Addressing" — the context and intent of the initiative in 2–4 sentences | This is the narrative field visible in the card view |
| Checkpoint Labels | Tags showing which maturity audit checkpoints this initiative addresses | Pulled from capability classification; user can add/remove |
| Milestone List | All milestones for this initiative as expandable rows with: name, owner avatar, month target visible in collapsed state | Inline quick-edit on click; full milestone modal on pencil icon |
| Inline Milestone Quick-Add | Plus button or empty row at bottom of milestone list | Same pattern as initiative quick-add in capability card |
| Add Milestone Button | Opens full milestone entry form | |

### Right Panel Content

| Element | Description | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Owner | Assigned team member or role accountable for this initiative | Dropdown or name entry |
| 3P Classification | Prioritize / Plant / Progressively Iterate tag | Editable — changing this updates backend metadata and breadcrumb |
| Target Completion | End-of-month target (month-level, not specific dates) | Dropdown: Month 1 / Month 2 / Month 3 |
| Status | Not Started / In Progress / At Risk / Blocked / Complete | Toggle selection; execution phase primary use |
| Sprint Goal Connection | The fourth field from the entry form, editable here | Visible reminder of why this initiative matters this quarter |
| Labels | Checkpoint tags and any custom labels | Add / remove |
| Change History | Log of edits made to this initiative with timestamps | Expandable; shows what changed and when |
| Comments & Activity | Founder and team member comments at initiative level | Timestamped; supports async team communication |

### Post-Milestone Edit Behavior

Once milestones exist under an initiative, all core initiative fields remain fully editable. If the "What Success Looks Like" field is updated after milestones have been created, the system prompts: "You've updated this initiative's outcome. Please review your milestones to ensure they still reflect this goal." This is a prompt, not a block. The founder decides what to do.

