## 8. Milestone Layer

Milestones are the evidence of progress for each initiative. They are strategic progress markers — not tasks. Each milestone represents a meaningful phase of completion that can be independently observed and verified.

> **Key distinction:** Milestones are NOT tasks ("Update the spreadsheet"). Milestones ARE strategic progress markers ("Dashboard live with accurate data"). Outcome describes the end state. Measure proves it happened.

### Milestone Fields

| Field | Description | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| Milestone Name | Short action-oriented label | e.g., "Audit current data sources" |
| Outcome | What the end state looks like when this milestone is complete | e.g., "Complete inventory of all data systems" |
| Measure | How we verify it is actually done | e.g., "All systems documented in shared sheet" |
| Owner | Who is accountable for this milestone | Dropdown — team member or role |
| Timeline | Which month this milestone targets | Dropdown: Month 1 / Month 2 / Month 3 |
| Dependencies | Which other milestones must be complete before this one can begin | Optional multi-select from other milestones in same initiative |
| Status | Not Started / In Progress / Complete / Blocked | Completing a milestone triggers maturity score update for associated checkpoints |
| Notes / Blocker Flag | Optional free text for context, blockers, or updates | Inline on milestone card |

### Milestone Card Modal

Mirrors the initiative card pattern. Left panel shows the milestone detail fields (outcome, measure, notes, blocker flag). Right panel shows owner, timeline, dependencies, status, change history, and comments.

### Milestone Completion & Score Updates

When a founder marks a milestone complete, the system detects which maturity audit checkpoints that milestone's parent initiative addresses and updates those checkpoint scores accordingly. This is the closed-loop feedback mechanism that keeps the Maturity Dashboard current as execution progresses.

