## 9. Sprint Board Views

### By Capability View (Default)

Three columns (Prioritize / Plant / Progressively Iterate). Each column contains capability area cards. Each capability card shows:

- Capability name
- Stage tag (Below Stage / At Stage / Ahead of Stage)
- Initiative count ("2 Initiatives")
- Completion indicator if any initiatives are incomplete
- "Add Initiative" inline button below each card

Clicking a capability card opens the Capability Card Modal.

### By Initiative View (Toggle)

Same three columns. Each column now shows initiative cards directly. Each initiative card shows:

- Initiative name
- Progress bar (% of milestones complete)
- Owner avatar
- Milestone count ("3 of 5 milestones")
- Parent capability tag
- Completion indicator if initiative fields are incomplete

Clicking an initiative card opens the inline expand. Clicking the pencil icon opens the full Initiative Card Modal.

### Sprint Goal Banner

Persistent across both views. Displays the sprint goal statement in a visually distinct banner below the Sprint Board header. Always visible as founders work — the accountability anchor for everything being built below it.

### Sprint Synthesis Banner

When the sprint plan has been edited after a synthesis was last generated, a banner appears: "Your sprint synthesis may no longer reflect your current plan after recent edits." with Regenerate and Dismiss actions. Regenerate triggers a new GPT synthesis of the full plan at its current state.

### Parking Lot

A fourth column, not advertised prominently, that appears when a capability area has been placed outside the primary 9 selected. Labeled "Parking Lot" with the description "Not doing this right now. Safe to ignore." Used sparingly for edge cases where a founder identifies something relevant that falls outside their 9 classified areas. This column does not count against any 3P caps.

