## 10. Strategic Advisor Panel

### Purpose

A contextual AI chat window available throughout the sprint planning workflow. It provides coaching support, suggestions, and sense-checks on demand — without auto-generating content or consuming API credits unless the founder initiates.

### Behavior Principles

- Never auto-opens — founder must initiate
- Never auto-generates content — waits for founder prompt
- Context is always current: the advisor knows which capability, initiative, or milestone the founder is currently viewing
- Context updates as the founder drills deeper or navigates back in the modal hierarchy
- Suggested prompt chips appear at the bottom to lower activation energy

### Placement

| Location | Behavior |
|---|---|
| Sprint Board (main view) | Accessible via trigger icon in top-right of the board. Opens as right-side panel, compresses board layout. |
| Capability Card Modal | Accessible via icon anchored to bottom-right corner of the modal. Opens as embedded chat panel within the modal without closing it. |
| Initiative Card Modal | Same bottom-right corner anchor pattern as capability card. |
| Milestone Card Modal | Same pattern. |

### Contextual Awareness by Level

| Level | Context Available |
|---|---|
| Sprint Board | Sprint goal, 3P classification, all capability areas selected, overall initiative count and completion status |
| Capability Card | All Sprint Board context + which capability is open, its maturity score, its checkpoint context, existing initiatives |
| Initiative Card | All above + initiative name, fields populated, milestone count and status |
| Milestone Card | All above + milestone name, outcome, measure, owner, dependencies |

### Example Suggested Prompts by Level

**Sprint Board level:**
- "Help me translate my Prioritize capabilities into initiatives"
- "What does focusing on these three areas imply for my quarter?"

**Capability Card level:**
- "Suggest initiatives for this capability area at my stage"
- "What does good look like here for an agency like mine?"

**Initiative Card level:**
- "Does this initiative connect clearly to my sprint goal?"
- "Suggest milestones for this initiative"
- "Are there any risks I should flag here?"

