## 13. Data & Backend Notes

> **IMPORTANT:** The Architect OS backend (Supabase schema, scoring engine, n8n automations) is complete and must not be modified. All front-end components read from and write to existing backend structures. This section notes only the data relationships the front-end must respect.

- 3P classification is stored as metadata on each capability selection record — the front-end reads this to populate columns and breadcrumbs
- Initiative records link to capability area records via foreign key — breadcrumb cascade reads this relationship
- Milestone completion events trigger checkpoint score updates — front-end fires this event; backend handles score recalculation
- Incomplete status is a front-end computed state based on field population — not a stored database field
- Sprint lock creates a point-in-time snapshot record — the executive summary is stored against this snapshot
- Strategic Advisor panel calls are user-initiated GPT calls — not automated or triggered by platform events
- All five initiative fields map to columns in the existing initiatives table — no new schema required

